Commentary Text: Chris Morris to Ferguson, out Kuldeep Yadav Run Out!! 1 run completed. Just short and gone! Low full toss on the pads, Ferguson chips it over mid-wicket and calls for two straightaway, the fielder in the deep was quick to gather and he sends a flat throw at the bowling end where Morris completes the rest to catch Kuldeep an inch short of his crease. Too close. Kuldeep Yadav run out (Gurkeerat Singh/Chris Morris) 12(19) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Karthik, out Lbw!! A googly, Karthik plays for the leggie and is rapped on the pads. A big shout for lbw, not given. Kohli signals 'T' with 2 seconds left. Three reds on HawkEye and DK has to go. This is a brilliant review from RCB! The right-handed batsman pressed forward to block and played outside the line of it. The ball spun in a tad to rap him adjacent to middle and leg. Ball-tracking showed it to be hitting leg. Chahal strikes in his first over! Karthik lbw b Chahal 4(14)

Commentary Text: Siraj to Nitish Rana, out Bowled!! Timber! Two in two for Mohammed Siraj. Dream start for RCB. An inswinger, no extravagant movement, but enough to trouble the batsmen. Nitish Rana is half-forward to push it into the off-side. Doesn't account for the inward movement and ends up playing outside the line. The ball curls in through the bat-pad gap to knock off the off-stump. There was a leg gully put in place just as Rana came in, which might've played with his mind. Nitish Rana b Siraj 0(1)

Commentary Text: Ferguson to Finch, out Caught by Karthik!! Ferguson among the wickets immediately yet again. Just behind a good length around off, Finch is hesitant to come forward to it. He remains in the crease and tries to punch into the off side, edging it through in the process. It's Ferguson's fourth wicket in the tournament already, in 4.2 overs. Probably should've taken the new ball here. Finch c Karthik b Ferguson 16(21) [4s-2]
